					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1436137&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252342" alt="fieldstone" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1436137)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fieldstone" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1436137); return false;" >fieldstone</a></span> <span class="odate time_1537110733 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Sep 2018 15:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3972515">
									

<p>You had me at</p>
<blockquote>
<p>it's deeply unpleasant</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&lt;3</p>
<p>I appreciate you letting me know you still thought it was well written! I knew I'd get a lot of negative reactions along these lines and fully expect this to be my last round, but when I was given a prompt to make these two characters interact, the thing pretty much wrote itself.</p>
<p>You're right that this wouldn't exist without the contest - these are different interpretations of the Foundation that aren't meant to go together, and inflicting Johnson on someone else's characters unprovoked would just be rude. But in this context, I took it as a challenge to come up with the coldest shit possible. In that regard I'm happy with how it came out, and the contest was a fun inspiration.</p>

							</div>

								
					
